		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/06/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 17:39:49</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=6149"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=6149')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=6891&amp;FORUM_ID=6&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=The+Great+Necro+Talks+2002&amp;Topic_Title=Letter+to+Scott%2C+hopefully+he%27ll+consider"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Following is a letter I sent to Scott after he was nice enough to drop by and give us an update on DOT stacking.</P><P>The necro community really appreciates you stopping by to give us the update that DOT stacking is still on the table.  Necros as a class usually feel left out and Alan's idea of PR just makes this worse.  Focus items overall did very little to help necromancers and (no offense) were badly implemented (ie. ones for 44+ spells off VERY high-level mobs or assigned to items that no longer drop in game, dont help our DPS and most of our DD's are unaffected because of stun or other effects).  When we state our concerns, Alan's answers always talk a lot.. but never say anything.  The clearcut answer you gave us breaks a long tradition of keeping us in the dark.</P><P>The pet changes have been awesome.  Our pets are substantial fighters again, and can actually stand against a mob long enough for us to get a second spell off if the first one was resisted. </P><P>The new UI is a 100% improvement over the old one, except for items poofing.. but we expect that will be fixed soon.  It makes so many things better/easier that I wouldn't dream of going back to the old one.</P><P>After DOT stacking, our primary issues are getting more DPS for our DOTs as this will actually make them worth casting in a group.  Perhaps critical DOTs since we cant crit our other spells and we're supposted to be DOT masters.</P><P>Essence emeralds are a joke.  They are never used (who will just give up 3 hours of EXPing so you can cast one spell?).  A better way is to perhaps make the spells so the EE isn't used up.  Leave the ungodly refresh times if you must.  You could even make the spell "Sacrifice" self only.  Then, once we sacrificed those hours of our EXP, we could cast the other spells that require the EE (similar to how black pearl isn't consumed).</P><P>Our last major issue is with the Lich line.  We've become used to the fact that our hp/mana ratio doesn't significantly improve, but are unsure why our mana regen is the only one that doesn't stack with clarity.  Clarity line stacks with Wizzie regen (with pet), shammy cannibalize line, and mages modrod.  I understand why it stacks with them, and am glad they have it, but am still unsure why it doesn't stack for us as well.</P><P>If you are reading this, I truly appreciate the time you took to read this.  As I stated before, as a whole, necromancers feel overlooked in most of the changes and it was great to see VI addressing the one issue that makes more than 1 necro on a raid a social faux pas.</P><P>Thanks in advance,<BR>Dalamarn Darkgem<BR>Necromancer Extraordinaire</P><P> </font></td>

      </tr>

