         Great letter that nicely sums up most of our issues. I especially like your points about the fact that Lich does not stack with clarity. We pay for our mana with our health--just as a shaman does. Yet a shaman can have clarity on and bardsongs and cannibalize at the same time. </P><P>Again we get screwed by Verant on a stacking issue. I don't think any other class is more adversely affected by stacking issues than the necromancers. Many times our Luclin group buffs will not stack on players are they have run out of buff slots. We are the victims of poor game design and poor coding.</P><P>Dornette<BR>60 necromancer<BR>The Nameless<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
