        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Thank you.  I agree about all of our stacking problems.  No reply back of course, but hopefully he at least read it and will take it into consideration.  I was so happy to see him give us a definate that they're still looking at DOT stacking (especially after Absor blows smoke up our asses with every post).  For once we got a post that didn't take 5 lines to say absolutely nothing.  Aside from pet changes (which are awesome IMHO), caster balance pretty much left us in the dark.  As others have stated, we now have no means to get these addressed.  I dont understand why an entire class tells them something is wrong for 3 years, and still nothing is done about it.</P><P>1)Do the focus items help us?  Not really, if I was a wizzie or a mage I would be loving them.  <BR>2)Everyone else gets increased damage output, but us (aside from pet is now max level so you dont have to spend 5 minutes resummoning).  <BR>3)Why cant we crit?  <BR>4)Why do SKs have better FD than us.. their parent class?<BR>4)Why are our resists so high that mages and wizards 4 and 5 levels beneath me land spells on things I cant?<BR>5)Why do they leave in the rediculous line of EE spells when the whole class tells them that we dont use them?<BR>6)Why do they put equipment on "uber" mobs that 98% of the server will never see and tell us that we're balanced because of it.<BR>7)Why when I've been liching for 50+ levels does my ratio not significantly improve?<BR>8)Why when I've been giving mana for so many levels, do we not get a better ratio?<BR>9)Why do soooo many of our spells not only not stack with each other, but OTHER classes as well?</P><P>This isn't a bitch/whine list (and I know it's far from complete).. it's a list of serious subjects we have that people refuse to address.  We're continually overlooked and have no effective outlet to be heard.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
